  "title": "Payment Gateway Partner (PSP)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Build and maintain strong relationships with local banks and payment institutions in South Korea, with a solid understanding of the country’s financial landscape and payment systems.</li>\n  <li>Possess in-depth knowledge of the operations and applications of local payment methods, including bank transfers and e-wallets, particularly in high-risk industries.</li>\n  <li>Communicate and liaise effectively with local banks and payment partners to ensure smooth collaboration.</li>\n  <li>Negotiate with payment service providers (PSPs) to secure competitive service fees and exchange rates.</li>\n  <li>Maintain the stability, reliability, and diversity of payment gateway channels.</li>\n  <li>Propose and implement incentive programs or promotional schemes to enhance performance.</li>\n  <li>Handle other ad-hoc tasks or assignments as required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor in Banking/ Finance or any related field.</li>\n  <li>Working experience in local banks and payment institutions in South Korea</li>\n  <li>Experience in handling inbound/outbound payments including fiat and crypto</li>\n  <li>Sound knowledge of payment practices in market</li>\n  <li>Interests in cryptocurrency products</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Interested applicants for the above advertised position(s), please kindly email an updated copy of your resume to: <strong>gs1@talenttradersg.com;</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No.: 13C6305</p>\n<p>Registration No.: R23117856 CHOE KIN MUN</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>For candidate who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p>",
